cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video segmentation and object detection. The use of a Moving Objectness Detector also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of figure-ground segmentations and motion affinities suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of random walkers on motion affinities suggests a potential focus on robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
